# -1 save/restore win size/pos (in songbird.sbc)
#0
# File->New | Open | Open Recent-> | Close | Save | Save As... | Backup |
#   Import (e.g., from CSV/TSV/etc) | Export (e.g. to CSV/TSV/etc + dump) |
#   Quit
#1 pure SQL
#2 custom types via Tcl functions (e.g., tobytes, frombytes, tosring)
#3 custom forms
#5 ultimately aim to be able to replace both Biller and Notebox with
#  custom songbird databases

# Not SDI: for multiple dbs run multiple instances.
# Main window layout:
#
#   Menu bar.................
#   Tool bar.................
#   Contents tree is a dock window
#   Central area is MDI for Form/List views
#   Status bar.....................

# Toggle Form View toggles between a form for adding/editing and a list
# for viewing (and possibly in-place adding/editing).
# Toggle Tabs toggles between MDI and tabs view.

#  &Edit         &SQL                &Options	      
#    &Copy ^C      Create &SELECT...    [X] Show &Contents   
#    Cu&t  ^X      ---------            [ ] Show C&alendar   
#    &Paste ^V     Create &Table...     [ ] Show Calc&ulator 
#                  Create &View...       ------------------  
#                  &Create Trigger...   [X] Show &Toolbar
#                  ---------            ------------------  
#                  &Alter Table...      Toggle &Form View   
#                  Alter Vie&w...       &Toggle Tabs        
#                  A&lter Trigger...    ------------------  
#                                       &Options...         

# &Window             
#   &Next F6          
#   &Previous Shift+F6
#   &1 <mdi name>                   
#      :	                    
#   &9 <mdi name>      
#   &More ->           
#   ---------          
#   &Close Ctrl+W

# Initially insert/update can only be done in form view and delete in
# form or list view. Ideally allow in-place insert/update in list view
# if/when possible.

